---
source: tests/cli.rs
expression: help
---
Create a request immediately; acceptance syntax is reserved but unavailable

Usage: request --note <NOTE> <RECIPIENT> <AMOUNT>
       request accept [OPTIONS] <REQUEST_ID>
       request help [COMMAND]...

Arguments:
  <RECIPIENT>
          Exact @username or positive numeric Venmo user ID

  <AMOUNT>
          Positive USD amount with at most two fractional digits

Options:
      --note <NOTE>
          Non-empty request note

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

request accept:
Reserved request-acceptance syntax; this operation is unavailable
      --from <METHOD_ID>
          Preferred external/backup method ID; Venmo balance may be used first

      --yes
          Skip only the final default-No confirmation

  -h, --help
          Print help

  <REQUEST_ID>
          Canonical incoming request ID

request help:
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
  [COMMAND]...
          Print help for the subcommand(s)

Direct request creation writes immediately after validation. It does not prompt and has no `--yes` option. Financial exit code 3 means the request outcome must be verified independently. Do not retry; check `requests list` and the official Venmo app.
